caption: Food is definitely overpriced but the sushi chef was very funny to make it up. I wouldn’t recommend the bone marrow, though. Had a good time.

I never really cared for uni until I had it here.  Sweet, delicate, and melts away on the pallet.  Every time I've had it it's been briny and just nasty.  Really glad my friends brought me here.  The wait staff was also very knowledgeable and friendly.  However, it's scary easy to rack up a tab here cause the food is so on point.

If you're looking for a yummy place for Japanese food - this is your place. Love the 'hidden' location tucked away off Keeaumoku St. Sushi ii is an izakaya (drinks+food) and sushi bar. Excellent service. Food is delicious, Have to order the hamachi kama - so tender and perfectly seasoned. Call ahead and make a reservation. Visited in Nov 2020 and the restaurant is practicing social distancing , safety measures. We felt very comfortable and safe throughout our experience.

Everything was good. Our server was amazing and I loved her green hair. We ordered bone marrow with roasted eggplant & garlic, pan seared foie gras, king salmon kama, escargot, misoyaki butterfish, crispy fried shrimp, grilled abalone, sushi, fried taco, and ama ebi sweet shrimp.

Sushi ii is a gem of a place with amazingly fresh fish that's fed to you one by one by the chef if you sit at the bar. Daily specials are to die for, especially the bone marrow with eggplant and the ikura on toast with creme fraiche. They also have a good sake list and beer selection, including Suntory lager. They're very accomadating but I wouldn't go without a reservation. You shall not regret.

On a tight schedule, I asked for eight pieces over thirty minutes. Like a Tsukiji breakfast.  I ordered a bottle of ten year old barrel aged shochu, Kagoshima's Mugon, 40abv.  Steve started me with tai that had been covered with cloth and shocked with hot water, then topped with yuzu kosho.  Then some kombu cured hirame, sweet and fatty shima aji, followed by the belly part of a kampachi.  Kinmedai shocked with hot water like the tai, and slightly torched on the skin for a hint of smoke, ikura gunkan , an aburi red prawn from Argentina covered with kanimiso - torching removed the funkiness of the kanimiso and added intense flavor to the prawn.  The finish was aburi engawa, accented with lemon and sea salt.  Steve dropped a couple of irregular cuts of chutoro and jellyfish in ponzu topped with momiji oroshi as dessert.  Awesome! I should do this more often.

A complete waste of time and money for the sushi lover (if you've ever had fresh, delicious sushi, stay FAR away from this place!) The people are nice, service was friendly, and the sushi chefs...umm cut the frozen fish nice... and then... maybe they use a wizard to magically remove all flavor??
Definitely a great place for sushi.  They also have a lot of great dishes and have plenty of specials to keep you coming back for more!

Went in for the omakse, and it was great. Chef finished it off with fatty tuna, wagyu beef, and foie gras. Super rich and fatty, and was a delicious end to a great meal. Had no reservations and to wait an hour for a seat. We shopped at Walmart and by the time we were done we were able to eat.
